    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - REMOVE - SPLITTER CYLINDER ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>SPLITTER CYLINDER ASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>To remove the splitter cylinder assembly, you must be able to access the front and rear of the
                    auxiliary case.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>When removing the splitter cylinder cover insert valve, note the direction the insert valve was
                    positioned (nipple in or out).
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the retaining bolts from the splitter cylinder cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300761">Figure 61</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300761" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300761" filename="../figg13/g1300761.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 61. Remove Retaining Bolts From Splitter Cylinder Cover</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the cover and gasket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300761">Figure 61</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 3/4 inch nut on the splitter yoke bar (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300762">Figure 62</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300762" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300762" filename="../figg13/g1300762.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 62. Remove Nut on Splitter Yoke Bar</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the sliding clutch and shift yoke straight out to remove them from the auxiliary front
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300763">Figure 63</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300763" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300763" filename="../figg13/g1300763.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 63. Pull Sliding Clutch and Shift Yoke Straight Out</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the splitter cylinder housing from the auxiliary rear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300764">Figure 64</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300764" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300764" filename="../figg13/g1300764.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 64. Remove Splitter Cylinder Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the insert valve retaining nut and insert valve from the splitter cylinder cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300765">Figure 65</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300765" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300765" filename="../figg13/g1300765.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 65. Remove Insert Valve</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the insert valve and cover bore for damage.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the piston O-rings; replace if necessary.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the small O-ring inside the cylinder housing bore; replace if necessary.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
